# Theme & Notification Patterns

## Theme Colors

All colors are centralized as `$script:` variables in `Initialize-Theme.ps1`. Categories:
- `MenuButton*` / `MenuButtonOnClick*` — menu bar normal + pressed states
- `MenuButtonShowIcon` / `MenuButtonSeparator` — icon prefix toggle and char
- `MenuButtonShowBrackets` / `MenuButtonBracket*` — bracket wrapping
- `DialogButton*` — dialog action button icon/bracket settings
- `Header*` / `Footer*` — chrome group backgrounds
- `HeaderRowBg` / `MenuRowBg` — per-row inset backgrounds
- `BorderPadV` / `BorderPadH` — blank-row/column border thickness
- `*Dialog*` — per-dialog color sets (Quit, Settings, Time, Move, Info, Options)

When adding new theme colors:
1. Add `$script:NewColor = "..."` in `Initialize-Theme.ps1`
2. Use via `Write-Buffer -FG $script:NewColor`
3. Update `AGENTS.md` color categories table

## Emoji Handling

Emojis display as 2 columns but have string length 1. Compute positions statically:
```powershell
$emojiX = $startX
$pipeX = $emojiX + 2  # Emoji takes 2 display columns
Write-Buffer -X $emojiX -Y $row -Text $emoji -FG $color -BG $bg -Wide
Write-Buffer -X $pipeX -Y $row -Text "|" -FG $pipeColor -BG $bg
```

## Notification Fallback Chain

1. `$script:ToastAPI::ShowToast()` — native COM (instant)
2. `powershell.exe` subprocess — delegates to WinPS 5.1 WinRT support
3. `NotifyIcon.ShowBalloonTip()` — basic balloon (last resort)

Each toast uses a unique ephemeral AUMID (`svc_<PipeName>_<PID>_<seq>`). Registry key is created in `try`, toast fired, 50ms sleep, key removed in `finally`.

## Tray Icon

Background process only (`$script:_SkipTrayIcon = $true` in viewer). Uses `NotifyIcon` with `ContextMenuStrip` (Open, Pause/Resume, Quit). `DoEvents()` pumped every 50ms tick. `Update-TrayIcon` re-renders on title changes.

## Notification Bodies

Notification bodies must use `$script:WindowTitle` — never hardcoded internal terms ("Worker", "Viewer"):
```powershell
# CORRECT
Show-Notification -Body "$($script:WindowTitle) started (PID: $PID)" -Action started
Show-Notification -Body "$($script:WindowTitle) paused" -Action paused
Show-Notification -Body "$($script:WindowTitle) — terminal disconnected" -Action disconnected
```
